      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEKTRA BETA (1) boasts a strong record this journey with five wins and four minors from 11 tries. Comes off a (29.41) win last time, scoring by 3.5 lengths in a Grade 5 over 515m at Sandown. Rates on top and should go close. KEEP ROLLING (7) boasts a strong record this journey here with three wins and two minors from nine tries. Below best last time at Ballarat (30.89) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 7 length fourth. Can hit the frame with the right run. NO DO DAY (2) struggled to get involved last start after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won by one length at this track (30.32) beating Impress Moana in a Grade 5 on March 7. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Must be included in calculations. PAW ULTRA (3) was strongly fancied last time on the back of some good form but finished third (25.38) at Ballarat. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from six starts. Ready to find winning form.",
